WEBVTT

00:00:06.870 --> 00:00:09.320
<i>Suzuka-san, why…</i>

00:00:10.610 --> 00:00:11.810
Come in.

00:00:12.870 --> 00:00:14.740
Do you have some time right now, Pony-chan?

00:00:14.740 --> 00:00:15.570
Yeah.

00:00:15.570 --> 00:00:18.410
You've gotten a call from
El Condor Pasa in France.

00:00:19.070 --> 00:00:20.910
El-chan?

00:00:21.890 --> 00:00:22.840
Hello?

00:00:22.840 --> 00:00:26.280
<i>Hmm? I thought you'd be depressed
after you lost to Grass,</i>

00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:27.420
<i>but you sound like
you're doing well.</i>

00:00:27.760 --> 00:00:30.260
Guess I didn't need to call you.

00:00:30.260 --> 00:00:31.940
You were worried about me?

00:00:32.840 --> 00:00:33.920
Thank you.

00:00:34.230 --> 00:00:35.720
<i>Are you doing well, El-chan?</i>

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:37.160
<i>Are you eating well?</i>

00:00:37.160 --> 00:00:38.930
I'm doing great!

00:00:38.930 --> 00:00:41.600
I've been working on bulking up
for the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe,

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:43.180
and I've gotten even bigger now.

00:00:44.170 --> 00:00:46.250
El-chan, you know exactly
what you want, don't you?

00:00:46.250 --> 00:00:47.440
Of course!

00:00:47.440 --> 00:00:50.910
I'm going to win in the Prix de
l'Arc de Triomphe, no matter what.

00:00:50.910 --> 00:00:54.210
That's why I want you to tell Suzuka-san
that she'll be able to win again,

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:56.450
since she beat me in the past,
and I'm really good.

00:00:57.960 --> 00:01:00.040
Y-Yeah, I'll tell her.

00:01:00.570 --> 00:01:02.690
Anyway, make sure you don't get sick or hurt.

00:01:02.690 --> 00:01:04.660
<i>Sure! Talk to you later.</i>

00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:12.740
<i>I guess there isn't anything
else I can do for her.</i>

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:20.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:01:23.740 --> 00:01:28.960
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:01:28.960 --> 00:01:35.490
I want to see that shining future with you

00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:43.830
{\an8}Umamusume

00:01:39.410 --> 00:01:43.700
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:51.440
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:56.460
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:01:56.460 --> 00:02:02.070
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:02:02.070 --> 00:02:08.930
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:02:09.740 --> 00:02:14.930
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:22.210
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:02:22.210 --> 00:02:27.630
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:02:27.630 --> 00:02:33.100
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:33.100 --> 00:02:38.610
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:02:38.610 --> 00:02:46.370
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:02:48.020 --> 00:02:52.020
{\an8}Race 9

00:02:48.020 --> 00:02:52.020
{\an8}Dreams of Spica

00:02:57.490 --> 00:03:00.320
<i>You're going to be the best
horse girl in Japan, right?</i>

00:03:00.320 --> 00:03:02.450
You don't have time to pay
attention to other things.

00:03:02.450 --> 00:03:05.160
That's right.

00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:10.120
<i>I guess telling her not to worry
about Suzuka wouldn't help.</i>

00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:13.130
{\an7}Summer Dream
Trophy Special

00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:13.130
{\an9}Team Rigil Trainer
Toujou Hana
Exclusive interview!

00:03:13.540 --> 00:03:16.310
My team is all over the place right now.

00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:19.130
Hey, Suzuka.

00:03:20.290 --> 00:03:21.220
Hey.

00:03:24.290 --> 00:03:26.120
What did the doctor say?

00:03:26.630 --> 00:03:28.930
My leg seems to be all better now.

00:03:28.930 --> 00:03:30.400
I see.

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:32.710
Then you're completely recovered.

00:03:32.710 --> 00:03:34.810
Just in time for our training camp.

00:03:35.750 --> 00:03:36.660
Hmm?

00:03:36.660 --> 00:03:37.570
What's wrong?

00:03:38.090 --> 00:03:40.680
I wonder if I'm getting in the way.

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:41.970
In the way?

00:03:41.970 --> 00:03:44.820
Others are slowing down so that
I can keep up with them,

00:03:44.820 --> 00:03:47.420
and as a result, they're
holding themselves back.

00:03:47.420 --> 00:03:48.950
You mean Spe?

00:03:48.950 --> 00:03:50.580
You too, Trainer-san.

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:54.580
You've been watching after
me constantly lately.

00:03:58.800 --> 00:04:01.690
You don't need to worry about that.

00:04:01.690 --> 00:04:03.130
R-Right.

00:04:16.450 --> 00:04:17.280
It's the ocean!

00:04:17.280 --> 00:04:18.880
I wanna see, too!

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:20.190
You two are like kids.

00:04:20.190 --> 00:04:23.560
I don't like the beach because
sea breeze damages the skin.

00:04:23.560 --> 00:04:24.780
Yeah.

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:33.790
This hotel's amazing!

00:04:33.790 --> 00:04:35.910
This is pretty nice.

00:04:35.910 --> 00:04:37.040
That's…

00:04:37.780 --> 00:04:39.500
The girls from Rigil!

00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:41.670
They're doing a training camp, too?!

00:04:41.670 --> 00:04:42.600
Really?!

00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:44.260
I finally get to be with the president!

00:04:44.260 --> 00:04:48.850
There's a chance we'll get to see them run
from up close since we're at the same hotel.

00:04:48.850 --> 00:04:50.920
Hey, where are you going?

00:04:50.920 --> 00:04:52.570
We're staying over there.

00:04:55.370 --> 00:04:56.420
What?

00:04:57.150 --> 00:04:58.580
You're kidding, right?

00:04:58.580 --> 00:05:00.070
It's pretty run down…

00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:03.640
Meet up at the front after
you drop off your stuff.

00:05:03.640 --> 00:05:05.570
Seriously?

00:05:05.570 --> 00:05:07.870
{\an7}Team A
Special Week
Vodka
Tokai Teio
Mejiro McQueen

00:05:07.170 --> 00:05:08.790
Huh? What's this?

00:05:07.780 --> 00:05:09.530
{\an9}Team B
Silence Suzuka
Gold Ship
Daiwa Scarlet

00:05:09.880 --> 00:05:10.840
What's going on?

00:05:10.840 --> 00:05:12.540
Teams?

00:05:12.540 --> 00:05:16.830
We're going to do this summer's
training camp in two teams.

00:05:16.830 --> 00:05:18.530
Two teams…

00:05:19.480 --> 00:05:22.210
<i>I'm on a different team from Suzuka-san.</i>

00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:25.880
And the theme for this camp is…

00:05:25.380 --> 00:05:27.470
{\an8}No Being Friends

00:05:25.880 --> 00:05:27.470
"No being friends"?

00:05:27.470 --> 00:05:30.100
I want the two teams to
compete against each other,

00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:33.810
and focus on training.

00:05:34.570 --> 00:05:36.940
We're having a match on
the last day of the camp.

00:05:36.940 --> 00:05:38.170
That's all.

00:05:39.430 --> 00:05:43.240
One… two…

00:05:43.240 --> 00:05:45.540
Why can't we be friends?

00:05:45.540 --> 00:05:47.360
Actually, did we ever get along?

00:05:47.360 --> 00:05:51.150
Well, at the bare minimum,
Scarlet and I haven't gotten along.

00:05:51.150 --> 00:05:51.830
But…

00:05:51.830 --> 00:05:56.330
{\an8}Gensen Kakenagashi
Quality Hot Springs

00:05:52.620 --> 00:05:55.210
Why are you looking my way?

00:05:55.210 --> 00:05:56.330
Well, you know…

00:06:06.470 --> 00:06:08.920
You call <i>that</i> being friendly?!

00:06:08.920 --> 00:06:10.440
Yeah, I do.

00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:10.970
Yeah.

00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:15.240
I wonder if that means Suzuka-san
and I were getting along.

00:06:15.240 --> 00:06:17.230
I'd imagine so.

00:06:17.230 --> 00:06:21.200
Is that a bad thing?

00:06:21.200 --> 00:06:26.860
Spe-chan, I know you're worried about Suzuka,
but you need to focus right now.

00:06:26.860 --> 00:06:28.290
Yeah.

00:06:28.290 --> 00:06:30.340
Gold Ship isn't here right now, either.

00:06:30.340 --> 00:06:32.070
Let's all have fun running.

00:06:32.070 --> 00:06:33.210
Yeah!

00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:36.870
Come on, Spe-chan. Let's go.

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:53.320
Her leg has healed, right?

00:06:53.320 --> 00:06:57.410
Yeah, but she doesn't want to
get in our way, supposedly.

00:06:57.410 --> 00:06:59.020
Huh? In our way?

00:07:12.610 --> 00:07:13.870
Hey!

00:07:13.870 --> 00:07:16.200
Let's run together.

00:07:16.200 --> 00:07:18.260
It's boring running by yourself, isn't it?

00:07:19.620 --> 00:07:22.080
Or is your leg still…

00:07:23.930 --> 00:07:26.170
It doesn't hurt at all.

00:07:26.170 --> 00:07:28.440
It doesn't hurt, but…

00:07:28.440 --> 00:07:30.210
Are you okay?

00:07:30.210 --> 00:07:33.930
Yeah, just leave me alone for a bit.

00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:42.440
{\an7}Unjoukaku

00:07:42.440 --> 00:07:44.600
I can't eat any more…

00:07:44.600 --> 00:07:46.590
I simply couldn't eat another bite…

00:07:46.590 --> 00:07:48.980
I just can't eat more…

00:07:48.980 --> 00:07:51.070
I can't eat any more…

00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:53.320
Naw, not eating any more…

00:07:58.950 --> 00:08:01.160
<i>Hi, trainer!</i>

00:08:01.160 --> 00:08:03.460
Sorry for bothering you while training.

00:08:03.460 --> 00:08:05.090
El, it's Rudolf.

00:08:05.090 --> 00:08:07.420
<i>Prez! What's up?</i>

00:08:07.420 --> 00:08:09.500
Suzuka has a message for you.

00:08:09.500 --> 00:08:10.880
She says, "Thank you."

00:08:10.880 --> 00:08:12.930
<i>Suzuka-san's all fired up, huh?</i>

00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:16.260
Now I really can't lose the
Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.

00:08:17.250 --> 00:08:18.280
That's the spirit.

00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:21.270
<i>Oh, yeah, the other day, I met Broye.</i>

00:08:21.270 --> 00:08:22.580
Broye?

00:08:22.580 --> 00:08:25.510
You mean the the horse girl they
call the best in Europe?

00:08:25.510 --> 00:08:26.400
<i>Yeah!</i>

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:32.900
Thank you, everyone.

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:32.900
{\an7}Broye

00:08:32.900 --> 00:08:35.360
Don't push, everyone.

00:08:37.160 --> 00:08:39.910
Broye!

00:08:39.910 --> 00:08:41.530
Broye! Broye!

00:08:41.530 --> 00:08:43.430
Hey, Broye!

00:08:43.430 --> 00:08:45.920
Um… How are do you do?

00:08:46.740 --> 00:08:48.420
I'm feeling great.

00:08:50.500 --> 00:08:53.300
<i>She signed this.</i>

00:08:54.340 --> 00:08:56.340
She thought you were a fan, huh?

00:08:56.340 --> 00:08:58.010
<i>Seems so.</i>

00:08:58.010 --> 00:09:00.490
<i>But this could be a chance for me.</i>

00:09:00.490 --> 00:09:02.760
If she doesn't know me, then I
might be able to surprise her.

00:09:02.760 --> 00:09:03.520
<i>El?</i>

00:09:03.520 --> 00:09:04.060
Huh?

00:09:04.480 --> 00:09:07.150
Could you give me another
good look at her autograph?

00:09:07.150 --> 00:09:08.340
<i>Sure…</i>

00:09:12.980 --> 00:09:14.440
See you later!

00:09:14.850 --> 00:09:17.200
I won't lose to you, McQueen!

00:09:20.210 --> 00:09:22.760
<i>I need to stop worrying about Suzuka-san.</i>

00:09:22.760 --> 00:09:26.460
<i>But the more I think,
the more worried I get!</i>

00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:28.840
Man…

00:09:29.330 --> 00:09:30.520
Trainer-san…

00:09:30.520 --> 00:09:31.210
Hmm?

00:09:31.210 --> 00:09:32.510
What is it?

00:09:32.510 --> 00:09:34.280
Do you have a moment?

00:09:35.330 --> 00:09:37.110
You can't run at full speed?

00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:37.970
Yeah.

00:09:38.660 --> 00:09:39.690
Are you scared?

00:09:40.210 --> 00:09:43.100
I keep thinking I might hurt myself again.

00:09:43.990 --> 00:09:46.100
<i>So it's a mental thing.</i>

00:09:46.810 --> 00:09:51.230
Trainer-san, you told me in the hospital…

00:09:51.700 --> 00:09:56.480
You said that you didn't know if I'd be able
to race again, even if my leg healed.

00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:57.490
Yeah.

00:09:57.960 --> 00:10:00.900
This is what you were talking about, huh?

00:10:02.970 --> 00:10:06.500
<i>I'm going to have to do a
make-or-break move with this one…</i>

00:10:07.210 --> 00:10:09.860
<i>In order to push her to her limits…</i>

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:15.090
Oh? That's what you're going with?

00:10:13.270 --> 00:10:14.820
{\an7}Lowest
Card

00:10:15.090 --> 00:10:17.470
I'm not folding.

00:10:15.230 --> 00:10:17.190
{\an7}Lowest
Card

00:10:17.470 --> 00:10:20.700
And why are all of you so confident?

00:10:17.610 --> 00:10:20.700
{\an7}Lowest
Card

00:10:21.110 --> 00:10:23.910
{\an7}Second-Lowest
Card

00:10:22.550 --> 00:10:23.910
What are you doing, Spe-chan?

00:10:23.910 --> 00:10:24.770
Huh?

00:10:24.770 --> 00:10:26.600
Are you listening, Spe-chan?

00:10:26.600 --> 00:10:29.520
I think you should call.

00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:30.480
Yeah…

00:10:34.070 --> 00:10:35.530
I'm going to win!

00:10:58.230 --> 00:11:00.180
All right, now that you've
all gotten changed…

00:11:00.180 --> 00:11:03.430
I'm going to have you two teams have a match.

00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:05.680
We get to have a match on the beach?

00:11:05.680 --> 00:11:07.440
That sounds like fun!

00:11:07.440 --> 00:11:10.140
It won't be that easy.

00:11:10.140 --> 00:11:12.740
We're having a triathlon.

00:11:12.740 --> 00:11:13.560
Huh?

00:11:13.560 --> 00:11:15.360
A t-triathlon?

00:11:15.820 --> 00:11:17.840
You're going to swim
to that island over there,

00:11:17.840 --> 00:11:19.930
take a lap on a bicycle,

00:11:19.930 --> 00:11:22.820
and then run to the goal
at the bottom of the mountain.

00:11:22.820 --> 00:11:24.590
The training camp was fun.

00:11:24.590 --> 00:11:26.750
The food was pretty good, too.

00:11:26.750 --> 00:11:27.450
Wait!

00:11:27.450 --> 00:11:29.060
I'm giving the team that takes first

00:11:29.060 --> 00:11:32.870
a voucher for the dessert buffet
at the hotel Rigil's staying at.

00:11:32.870 --> 00:11:34.040
Dessert…

00:11:34.040 --> 00:11:35.460
…buffet?!

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:37.550
Now, everyone, let's have fun!

00:11:37.550 --> 00:11:38.740
Get ready—

00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:49.520
<i>Everyone's waiting for you to come back,</i>

00:11:50.410 --> 00:11:51.620
<i>Suzuka.</i>

00:11:53.020 --> 00:11:57.020
{\an4}Umamusume

00:11:53.020 --> 00:11:57.020
{\an4}Pretty Derby

00:12:00.850 --> 00:12:02.650
This is a serious match!

00:12:02.650 --> 00:12:05.160
Push yourselves and win!

00:12:06.450 --> 00:12:07.650
I won't let you!

00:12:23.140 --> 00:12:25.480
Dessert buffet!

00:12:25.480 --> 00:12:26.540
Get out of the way!

00:12:26.540 --> 00:12:28.180
I'm not losing to you, McQueen!

00:12:28.720 --> 00:12:29.140
Hey!

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:30.990
We're on the same team.

00:12:30.990 --> 00:12:33.230
That doesn't matter!

00:12:45.530 --> 00:12:48.410
Hey, are Spe and Suzuka okay?

00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:49.770
I wonder if they're exhausted.

00:12:49.770 --> 00:12:51.800
Do you have time to worry about someone else?

00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:53.210
Hey, wait up!

00:12:56.980 --> 00:12:58.360
Those guys…

00:13:06.550 --> 00:13:07.510
Suzuka-san!

00:13:07.510 --> 00:13:08.470
Spe…

00:13:09.240 --> 00:13:11.050
What are you doing?

00:13:11.540 --> 00:13:12.770
I'm going to help Suzuka-san.

00:13:12.770 --> 00:13:14.810
Are you going to stop in
the middle of a race?!

00:13:15.850 --> 00:13:19.440
Suzuka, is this the best you can do?!

00:13:19.440 --> 00:13:22.190
What was your promise about?!

00:13:23.090 --> 00:13:27.300
I'm going to make you keep your
promise of running with me.

00:13:27.820 --> 00:13:32.790
I want to see you two race together
and fight each other for first.

00:13:32.790 --> 00:13:34.830
That's my dream right now!

00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:39.480
You two want to help each other, right?

00:13:39.480 --> 00:13:40.990
Then think of each other as rivals,

00:13:40.990 --> 00:13:42.720
and lift each other up!

00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:44.010
Rivals…

00:13:44.010 --> 00:13:47.220
Spe, you want Suzuka
to race again, don't you?

00:13:48.420 --> 00:13:49.340
Yeah!

00:13:49.340 --> 00:13:52.020
Then run the hardest you can!

00:13:52.020 --> 00:13:54.440
You're supposed to give her
a target to catch up to!

00:13:54.980 --> 00:13:59.610
Suzuka, if you want to race again,
then you have to stop being scared!

00:13:59.610 --> 00:14:02.050
Don't be afraid to catch up to everyone!

00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:02.850
Right!

00:14:03.450 --> 00:14:05.110
Suzuka-san…

00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:09.960
I'm going to keep running.

00:14:17.320 --> 00:14:18.870
<i>Being Suzuka-san's rival…</i>

00:14:19.770 --> 00:14:21.880
<i>That's something I can do for her!</i>

00:14:27.720 --> 00:14:30.820
<i>Spe-chan, I'm not going to lose.</i>

00:14:36.350 --> 00:14:38.770
I hope those two are okay.

00:14:44.280 --> 00:14:45.850
What? No way!

00:14:45.850 --> 00:14:46.840
Oh no!

00:14:46.840 --> 00:14:48.590
They're finally really coming at us!

00:14:48.590 --> 00:14:50.280
That's the way it's gotta be!

00:14:50.280 --> 00:14:52.030
No way!

00:14:52.030 --> 00:14:53.700
But I'm not letting you pass!

00:14:57.090 --> 00:14:58.850
<i>I can go faster!</i>

00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:15.260
<i>That's right.</i>

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:17.020
<i>This is the feeling…</i>

00:15:17.020 --> 00:15:19.780
We can't catch up!

00:15:21.160 --> 00:15:23.270
<i>Now that's Suzuka!</i>

00:15:28.860 --> 00:15:29.800
Huh?

00:15:30.520 --> 00:15:31.280
I need to stop…

00:15:31.280 --> 00:15:31.870
I…

00:15:31.870 --> 00:15:34.840
I can't stop!

00:15:34.840 --> 00:15:37.160
Neither can we!

00:15:40.490 --> 00:15:41.500
Are you guys okay?!

00:15:51.610 --> 00:15:52.980
Are you okay?!

00:15:56.850 --> 00:16:00.810
You guys are so dumb!

00:16:18.490 --> 00:16:22.120
It's been a while since
I've laughed this much.

00:16:25.650 --> 00:16:26.820
I was able to run.

00:16:28.920 --> 00:16:31.820
Both teams were disqualified,
but we all still get the prize!

00:16:31.820 --> 00:16:34.410
The trainer's a good guy sometimes.

00:16:34.410 --> 00:16:37.400
It was my first time seeing
Suzuka-san like that.

00:16:37.400 --> 00:16:39.640
"I can't stop!"

00:16:40.530 --> 00:16:41.560
Hey.

00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:46.140
Trainer-san, I'm going
to run with Suzuka-san.

00:16:46.140 --> 00:16:48.130
I'm going to make your dream come true.

00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:51.630
Um, are you listening?

00:16:51.630 --> 00:16:54.100
Trainer, is the food so good you want to cry?

00:16:54.100 --> 00:16:55.410
I…

00:16:55.860 --> 00:16:59.280
I want to see a race where
all of you can participate!

00:16:59.280 --> 00:17:03.290
An exciting race like we had today!

00:17:03.290 --> 00:17:05.670
You're going to fight each other as rivals,

00:17:05.670 --> 00:17:06.950
help each other get better,

00:17:06.950 --> 00:17:08.710
and then beat everyone!

00:17:08.710 --> 00:17:11.670
Team Spica is just getting started!

00:17:11.980 --> 00:17:12.840
Right!

00:17:27.510 --> 00:17:28.630
Is it time yet?

00:17:28.630 --> 00:17:30.070
Almost.

00:17:30.520 --> 00:17:33.400
The trainer couldn't come
into the girls' dorm, huh?

00:17:35.910 --> 00:17:39.910
<i>The horse girls await the race
in the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe.</i>

00:17:40.310 --> 00:17:44.250
<i>Even abroad, Japan's
El Condor Pasa is very popular.</i>

00:17:45.090 --> 00:17:47.050
She's like a movie star!

00:17:47.050 --> 00:17:51.460
I'm so jealous! She gets to run with
everyone in the world watching her!

00:17:51.460 --> 00:17:53.670
Win, El.

00:17:54.020 --> 00:17:58.440
Broye gave El her signature,
but what do you think she wrote?

00:17:58.440 --> 00:18:00.050
Just tell me already.

00:18:00.410 --> 00:18:04.060
"I can fly faster than you, Condor."

00:18:04.630 --> 00:18:07.010
I wonder if Broye's confidence will last.

00:18:11.010 --> 00:18:14.280
<i>I want to see how strong I am.</i>

00:18:14.280 --> 00:18:18.630
<i>I'm going to beat Broye and show
that I'm the best in the world.</i>

00:18:19.320 --> 00:18:22.580
<i>All the horse girls are entering their gates.</i>

00:18:30.630 --> 00:18:32.000
The race has started!

00:18:33.290 --> 00:18:34.500
She's off to a good start!

00:18:34.500 --> 00:18:35.950
Pretty good.

00:18:35.950 --> 00:18:37.720
She's better at getting
off the line than you.

00:18:37.720 --> 00:18:38.720
Hiss!

00:18:39.030 --> 00:18:40.680
<i>El Condor Pasa is taking a decisive lead!</i>

00:18:40.680 --> 00:18:41.970
<i>She's in front of the pack</i>

00:18:41.970 --> 00:18:43.970
<i>by a horse length!</i>

00:18:43.970 --> 00:18:45.740
Is El going stay in the lead?

00:18:45.740 --> 00:18:47.310
She's always in the middle, isn't she?

00:18:47.310 --> 00:18:51.310
Unlike in Japan, it's hard to get
out front once you're surrounded.

00:18:51.310 --> 00:18:52.760
It's a good plan.

00:18:53.650 --> 00:18:55.380
El-chan looks like she's having fun.

00:18:55.380 --> 00:18:56.400
Yeah.

00:18:56.730 --> 00:18:58.000
<i>They're making the third turn,</i>

00:18:58.000 --> 00:19:00.220
<i>and El Condor Pasa leads
by three horse lengths.</i>

00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:02.700
<i>Broye is in the middle of the pack.</i>

00:19:02.700 --> 00:19:06.540
{\an8}El Condor Pasa is in the lead,
with thirteen horse girls following her!

00:19:02.700 --> 00:19:05.030
I can't watch!

00:19:05.030 --> 00:19:06.540
Keep going!

00:19:06.540 --> 00:19:07.770
No, get further ahead!

00:19:07.770 --> 00:19:09.460
The stretch at the end is long!

00:19:09.460 --> 00:19:10.290
You can do it!

00:19:10.290 --> 00:19:13.040
<i>They're making the fourth turn,
and there are 500 meters left.</i>

00:19:13.040 --> 00:19:15.550
<i>El Condor Pasa is in the lead!</i>

00:19:15.550 --> 00:19:18.760
{\an8}El Condor Pasa is in the
lead by two horse lengths!

00:19:15.550 --> 00:19:16.780
They'll fight it out in the stretch!

00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:18.760
You're almost the best in the world!

00:19:18.760 --> 00:19:21.010
Go!

00:19:21.010 --> 00:19:25.510
El! El!

00:19:35.530 --> 00:19:36.610
It's Broye.

00:19:36.610 --> 00:19:37.900
She's made her move.

00:19:38.990 --> 00:19:40.790
One hundred meters left!

00:19:44.730 --> 00:19:46.280
They're battling it out!

00:19:46.280 --> 00:19:50.790
Broye's moved up!

00:19:52.790 --> 00:19:54.000
Pull away from her, El!

00:20:00.510 --> 00:20:01.870
<i>Broye's taken the lead!</i>

00:20:01.870 --> 00:20:03.650
<i>Broye's first over the finish line!</i>

00:20:03.650 --> 00:20:06.350
<i>El Condor Pasa's come in second!</i>

00:20:06.350 --> 00:20:10.180
<i>El Condor Pasa tried real hard out there,</i>

00:20:10.180 --> 00:20:12.680
<i>but in the last moments…</i>

00:20:12.680 --> 00:20:16.560
<i>Japan fell to France's Broye at the end.</i>

00:20:26.970 --> 00:20:28.600
{\an8}You were amazing.

00:20:46.430 --> 00:20:49.400
That was an great race, wasn't it, Spe-chan?

00:20:53.140 --> 00:20:56.610
<i>Wow, El-chan. You were really cool.</i>

00:21:07.860 --> 00:21:09.140
Special Week…

00:21:12.200 --> 00:21:13.400
President-san…

00:21:14.760 --> 00:21:16.840
Do you want to talk to her, too?

00:21:17.540 --> 00:21:18.790
{\an8}El Condor Pasa

00:21:18.790 --> 00:21:20.240
Sure!

00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:21.250
Hello?

00:21:22.450 --> 00:21:24.060
<i>Spe-chan, were you watching?</i>

00:21:24.060 --> 00:21:25.270
Yeah, I was!

00:21:25.270 --> 00:21:27.510
It's amazing you came in second!

00:21:27.510 --> 00:21:30.490
<i>I was in the lead until the end!</i>

00:21:30.490 --> 00:21:31.260
Yeah!

00:21:31.260 --> 00:21:33.110
<i>It felt great out there.</i>

00:21:33.110 --> 00:21:35.050
<i>I was in the lead at 100 meters,</i>

00:21:35.050 --> 00:21:37.930
<i>and I saw the finish line fifty meters out.</i>

00:21:37.930 --> 00:21:38.660
Yeah?

00:21:38.660 --> 00:21:41.270
<i>It was so close!</i>

00:21:41.270 --> 00:21:42.230
Yeah!

00:21:43.060 --> 00:21:49.240
<i>The world… was right in front of my eyes.</i>

00:21:49.240 --> 00:21:53.750
{\an8}El Condor Pasa

00:21:49.830 --> 00:21:52.450
<i>I was so close…</i>

00:21:54.440 --> 00:21:55.810
El-chan…

00:21:58.250 --> 00:22:01.750
{\an8}El Condor Pasa

00:22:09.370 --> 00:22:10.760
Are you going somewhere?

00:22:10.760 --> 00:22:12.810
I'm going to run!

00:22:12.810 --> 00:22:14.810
This late?

00:22:22.690 --> 00:22:24.020
I'll go with you.

00:22:25.700 --> 00:22:28.860
In a dash, in a flash,
just a little more now,

00:22:28.770 --> 00:22:31.600
each new race like a dream neverending

00:22:31.480 --> 00:22:34.410
Every one of us will blaze a
trail aimed right for the stars

00:22:34.290 --> 00:22:39.460
Together we'll run! Let's
go! Our starting gate!

00:22:48.590 --> 00:22:54.040
With curiosity in hand, go tug
on tomorrow's tail and say hello

00:22:53.920 --> 00:22:58.920
It's right there, so go on and close
the gap now (Right here and now!)

00:22:59.630 --> 00:23:05.110
Can't play by the rules they tell
you! Gotta learn it all by experience!

00:23:05.010 --> 00:23:09.950
If we just plan to run for the
end, everything will turn out okay!

00:23:10.110 --> 00:23:13.980
Can't get me down,
hesitate, or go too slowly!

00:23:15.730 --> 00:23:19.700
We know that deep in our hearts is a song

00:23:19.780 --> 00:23:22.920
that sings "give it your all"! Make it shine!

00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:26.860
In a dash, in a flash, just a
little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:26.720 --> 00:23:29.600
every step like the wind
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:29.470 --> 00:23:32.520
A twinkling star that we wear
on our sleeves (But only one!)

00:23:32.370 --> 00:23:34.790
Let's let our hearts race
together as one! (Grow up! Shine!)

00:23:34.670 --> 00:23:37.920
One more step, one more push,
just a little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:37.800 --> 00:23:40.560
each new race like a dream
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:40.450 --> 00:23:43.320
Every one of us will see
our path to the very end!

00:23:43.300 --> 00:23:49.030
Let's run now, everyone!
Let's go! Our starting gate!

00:23:50.305 --> 00:24:50.688
